      غِبْرٌ (assumed tropical:)  Rancour, malevolence, malice, or spite;
or concealed enmity and violent hatred: (K, TA:)
like غِمْرٌ. (TA.)


      مُغَلْغِلَةٌ, with kesr to the second غ, Hastening;
syn. مُسْرِعَةٌ [which is trans. and intrans.; but
generally the latter, like سَرِيعٌ]. (TA.)


      أَرْضٌ مُغْلَوْلِيَةٌ A land having abundant, and
dense or luxuriant, herbage; and with ع also;
i. q. مُغِمَّةٌ and مِغَمَّةٌ. (TA in art. غم.)


      6 
      تَغَاوَلُوا i. q. تَبَادَرُوا i. e. They hastened together;
vied, or strove, one with another, in hastening;
made haste to be, or get, before one another;
strove, one with another, to be first, or beforehand,
(comp. 3:) expl. by Freytag as meaning “ sese
invicem studuerunt capere. ”]


      غَائِظٌ Affecting with غَيْظ [or anger; or rage;
&c.; i. e. angering; or enraging; &c.]: (TA:)
pl. غَائِظُونَ. (Kur, xxvi. 55.)
